&#xa0;[bold]&#xa0;[bold]Written evidence submitted by Asylum Aid (LAI 002)[bold]&#xa0;[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]Asylum Aid is gravely concerned about the government’s proposed 
[normal]Legal Aid
[normal] reforms. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]These changes are likely to impact the human rights of some of Asylum Aid’s most vulnerable clients, including:
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]A
[normal]t the same time as removing access to justice from our clients, the proposals would immunise the government from challenges against its decisions. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]This will have deep, worrying and lasting implications for human rights in the UK.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
